---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Coffee — Café Terms That Score Big"
  description="Coffee terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. MOCHA (12pts), BARISTA (9pts), ESPRESSO (10pts). Coffee vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble coffee words, mocha scrabble points, barista scrabble, espresso scrabble word, cafe terms scrabble, coffee vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Coffee — Café Terms That Score Big","description":"Coffee terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. MOCHA (12pts), BARISTA (9pts), ESPRESSO (10pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-coffee"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is MOCHA a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! MOCHA scores 12 points (M=3, O=1, C=3, H=4, A=1). It combines M, C, and H tiles for strong 5-letter scoring. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play BARISTA in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. BARISTA scores 9 points (B=3, A=1, R=1, I=1, S=1, T=1, A=1) as a 7-letter word. As a potential bingo play (using all 7 tiles), it could earn the 50-point bonus for 59 total."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is ESPRESSO valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! ESPRESSO scores 10 points (E=1, S=1, P=3, R=1, E=1, S=1, S=1, O=1) as an 8-letter word. While the per-tile value is low, it uses common letters and can connect through existing board letters."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Coffee — Café Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Your morning brew doubles as Scrabble training. Coffee culture has given English dozens of Italian-origin words that use M, C, H, and B tiles effectively. MOCHA packs 12 points into just 5 tiles, while BARISTA offers bingo potential at 7 letters. Time to caffeinate your word game.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MOCHA (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ESPRESSO</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BARISTA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BREWED</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Perfect Shot</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">MOCHA — 12 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">M=3, O=1, C=3, H=4, A=1 · 5 letters · M+C+H combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A chocolate-flavoured coffee drink. MOCHA delivers 12 points from just 5 tiles — that's 2.4 points per tile, exceptional efficiency. It combines three mid-value consonants (M=3, C=3, H=4) with common vowels, making it very playable from typical rack draws.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Coffee Drinks & Styles</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">☕ ESPRESSO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · E=1, S=1, P=3, R=1, E=1, S=1, S=1, O=1 · Concentrated brew</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧑‍🍳 BARISTA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · B=3, A=1, R=1, I=1, S=1, T=1, A=1 · Coffee maker</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥛 LATTE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · L=1, A=1, T=1, T=1, E=1 · Milk coffee</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫘 BREWED</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · B=3, R=1, E=1, W=4, E=1, D=2 · Steeped coffee</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Roasting & Preparation</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BREWED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GROUND</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FILTER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ROASTED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PERCOLATE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Coffee Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MOCHA is a premium short word:</span> At 2.4 pts/tile, MOCHA outperforms many 7-letter words on efficiency. Play it on a double-word square for 24 points from just 5 tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BARISTA is bingo material:</span> At exactly 7 letters, BARISTA earns the 50-point bingo bonus (59 total). The letters B, A, R, I, S, T, A are all common — this bingo is very drawable.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BREWED deploys B+W:</span> When you hold B=3 and W=4 together (7 points), BREWED gives both tiles a home alongside common letters for 12 total points.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Coffee words excel at <span class="text-white font-medium">short, efficient scoring</span>. MOCHA (12pts/5 tiles) and BREWED (12pts/6 tiles) deliver premium-square-worthy scores without needing rare letters. BARISTA provides realistic bingo potential from common tiles. Keep these words ready for M+C+H racks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid coffee word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-chess/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Chess</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-maritime/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Maritime</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-textiles/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Textiles</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-ceramics/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Ceramics</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-jewelry/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Jewelry</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
